            ">"
        ]
    ]
}
```
</FILE_CONTENT>

This adds both pieces you asked for:

- language configuration support for `<` / `>`
- a lightweight `>` typing handler that inserts `</tag>` after `<tag>`

Notes:
- It works in `.convo` files directly.
- It also attempts to work inside injected convo regions in JS, Python, and Markdown by checking whether the cursor is currently inside an open convo block.
- It excludes closing tags, self-closing tags, declarations like `<!...>` and `<?...>`.

One important limitation:
- for JS template literals, this handler intentionally skips auto-close if it looks like the cursor is inside an unfinished `${...}` interpolation.

If you want, I can also tighten this further so it avoids inserting a closing tag when one already immediately follows the cursor, or make it smarter for nested tags across multiple lines.


